---
import PageHero from "../components/PageHero.astro";
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="Support - DemumuMind" description="How to get help with DemumuMind projects." currentPath="/support/">
  <div class="page-content">
    <PageHero
      eyebrow="Support"
      title="Procedural help, not a ticket maze."
      lede="Issues are the primary support path. Discussions are for broader questions. Security reports stay private."
      meta={["Issues first", "Private security reporting", "Org-wide discussions"]}
      proofItems={["Public bugs in issues", "Private vulns stay private", "Use-case details required"]}
      asideTitle="Support posture"
      asideBody="The fastest path to help is a reproducible report with environment and expected behavior, not an abstract complaint."
    />

    <h2>Filing an issue</h2>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>What you expected</strong> to happen.</li>
      <li><strong>What actually happened</strong>, including the error text.</li>
      <li><strong>How to reproduce it</strong> from a clean state.</li>
      <li><strong>Environment</strong>: OS, runtime version, and tool version.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Feature requests</h2>
    <p>
      Open an issue with the <code>enhancement</code> label and describe the use case, not only the proposed solution.
    </p>

    <h2>Security</h2>
    <p>
      Do not file vulnerabilities publicly. Use GitHub&apos;s private vulnerability reporting on the affected repository.
    </p>

    <h2>General questions</h2>
    <p>
      For questions that do not fit a bug report, use{" "}
      <a href="https://github.com/orgs/DemumuMind/discussions" rel="noopener">DemumuMind Discussions</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
